column17: [{"dateSeen":"2020-01-13T16:05:00.000Z","value":"Beautiful modern villa with one of the best view of Muscat bay above the cliffs, in a private luxury Shangri-La Hotel development. Located in Barr Al Jissah, 5 min from 5 stars hotels and all their amenities. Close to a traditional fishing village of Qantab, 10 minutes from the old Muttrah Souq. You will be able to enjoy the magnificent views of the area, it’s many activities and cultural discoveries. This is one of our 2 villa in this neighborhood. They're one next to each other. Situated on the Omani cliffs, the villa is fully equipped for your stay with spacious space. There are 4 bedrooms with 3 en-suite bathrooms, the 4th bedroom as access to one of the ensuite bathroom (across the corridor). All the bedrooms are furnished with a super king size bed and comfortable mattresses. Downstairs, you will find a large open space with fully equipped kitchen, dinner area and living room, all giving access onto the terrace with sea view where you can enjoy barbecues and meals outside. You will have full access to the villa to treat as your own, with a shared pool and recreation area (Pool & Ping-Pong tables) of the community. Private and closed garage for 2 car is available as well as outside parking outside. The entire house and garage. If you choose to have the maid services, she will occupy the maid's room downstairs which will be her private corner. We don’t live onsite but we are always a phone call away and we always have someone who is able to meet you for any queries you may have if we’re not available to meet. The villa is located in a very quiet neighborhood and gated community. A small marina is just a few minutes walk away for any boat trip/diving trip or we would be happy to introduce you to our Omani guide for private boat trip where you will be able to see the famous dolphins, sea-turtles and snorkel around the magnificent coast of the area. If you’re adventurous enough, the captain will show you how to catch squid for your dinner. If you’re not feeling like cooking, their is a large choice of restaurants at the walking distance (Shangri-La Hotels). They also offer tennis court, Spa, Gym and beach access with their daily pass (Access pass prices varies on the season and can be quite expensive). *** At the moment, a Marina development is being constructed below the cliff down from the villas. It’s usually not very noisy. The other permanent residents monitor noise levels daily and ensure it remains reasonable. *** A car is strongly recommended if you want to explore and visit as Muscat spread out along the shore over 60km. A EU or UK driving license is valid for up to 3 months provided you use a rental car. We can help you with better rates. Our area is an excellent jump out point for excursion, near highway leading to Sur or up to the mountains and the world class wadis (Canyon) of Oman."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2020-04-09T14:09:00.000Z","value":"A perfect gateway to your holiday of discovery. The room was designed in a way to offer you more comfort and to make you feel-like-home when you are away . Villa has 5 separate bedrooms with one hall access to kitchen and attached en suite bathroom with shower in each room. Rooms are interconnected for making separate rooms. Each room equipped with Fridge, LED TV, AC, Kettle etc. Basically it is an studio inside of a Villa being totally separate from the rest of the rooms. The highlight of the room is the view and the affordable price. My place is close to the airport and the city center. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and big groups. We will provide Free Airport Transfer from Khasab Airport"}]

Overall Eldho is a superb host, picking up and dropping off in his car whenever I needed. He organised the dhow cruise and helped me plan a hike too. The location is not quite as displayed on Airbnb - it’s about 5 km inland from the port area. However if you don’t have own transport this isn’t an issue as Eldho makes himself available to drive. Overall a really enjoyable stay and I’m glad I chose to stay here. Highly recommended!","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/16697487"],"username":"Mike"},{"date":"2019-06-08T09:59:42.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-10-22T02:00:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"Eldho is a great host !! He arrange transfer from Dubai on my first day also 2 tours the Dohow cruise and 4x4 mountain safari he really gives 100% into making sure your stay is hassle free! He even takes you out for dinner to the fish market to buy fresh fish then to the local restaurant to have it (Website hidden by Airbnb) day my diving school had a problem with transportation to the dive site so he took me into town so I could look around the old fort and I just called him when I needed a lift back. He is an incredible host! I’m new to using Airbnb so he as set the bar high for my following journey.","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/16697487"],"username":"Ian"},{"date":"2017-04-16T10:16:01.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-10-22T02:00:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"My stay at Altaif's place was absolutely great. Even better than expected and so convenient. I was only in Oman for 24 hours and Eldho was such a great host. He met us when we got lost on arrival (!) and showed us the way, drove us to a restaurant for dinner, made us breakfast and took us to the harbour the next day where he had organised a place for us on a boat tour. I couldn't have asked for more. Definitely stay here!! Thank you","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/16697487"],"username":"Isla"},{"date":"2018-08-21T11:15:46.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-10-22T02:00:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"This villa was bigger than I expected. 8 of us rented the whole place, all five rooms plus kitchen and living room, but we could have easily fit 4-7 more people comfortably. Eldho was very prompt in responding to any queries, and helped us get a great deal on the full day dhow cruise, complete with dolphin watching, snorkeling, and of course refreshments and buffet lunch included. Eldho also provided a continental breakfast of toast, coffee, jam and butter, which we supplemented with some eggs from the Lulu's hypermarket, which is just a 10-minute drive from the villa. Speaking of Eldho, he was a fantastic host‐‐I called him the fixer, as a huge compliment, because he can and will help with just about everything, including airport & local transport, arranging excursions (mountain, dhow and diving‐‐all great, excellent guides), and meals‐‐fish at local market, then to a restaurant for cooking (delicious and very cheap). column17: [{"dateSeen":"2019-11-02T00:31:00.000Z","value":"Beautiful modern villa with one of the best view of Muscat bay above the cliffs, in a private luxury Shangri-La Hotel development. Located in Barr Al Jissah, 5 min from 5 stars hotels and all their amenities. Close to a traditional fishing village of Qantab, 10 minutes from the old Muttrah Souq. You will be able to enjoy the magnificent views of the area, it’s many activities and cultural discoveries. This is one of our 2 villa in this neighborhood. They're one next to each other. Situated on the Omani cliffs, the villa is fully equipped for your stay with spacious space. There are 4 bedrooms with 3 en-suite bathrooms, the 4th bedroom as access to one of the ensuite bathroom (across the corridor). All the bedrooms are furnished with a super king size bed and comfortable mattresses. Downstairs, you will find a large open space with fully equipped kitchen, dinner area and living room, all giving access onto the terrace with sea view where you can enjoy barbecues and meals outside. You will have full access to the villa to treat as your own, with a shared pool and recreation area (Pool & Ping-Pong tables) of the community. Private and closed garage for 2 car is available as well as outside parking outside. The entire villa, it's garage and all living areas. We don’t live onsite but we are always a phone call away and we always have someone who is able to meet you for any queries you may have if we’re not available to meet. Maid services are available, both live in and daily cleaning. The villa is located in a very quiet neighborhood and gated community. A small marina is just a few minutes walk away for any boat trip/diving trip or we would be happy to introduce you to our Omani guide for private boat trip where you will be able to see the famous dolphins, sea-turtles and snorkel around the magnificent coast of the area. If you’re adventurous enough, the captain will show you how to catch squid for your dinner. If you’re not feeling like cooking, there is a large choice of restaurants at the walking distance (Shangri-La Hotels). They also offer tennis court, Spa, Gym and beach access with their daily pass (Access pass prices varies on the season and can be quite expensive). *** At the moment, a Marina development is being constructed below the cliff down from the villas. It’s usually not very noisy. The other permanent residents monitor noise levels daily and ensure it remains reasonable. *** A car is strongly recommended if you want to explore and visit as Muscat spread out along the shore over 60km. A EU or UK driving license is valid for up to 3 months provided you use a rental car. We can help you with better rates. Our area is an excellent jump out point for excursion, near highway leading to Sur or up to the mountains and the world class wadis (Canyon) of Oman."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2020-04-09T13:30:00.000Z","value":"Soak up the modern and bright charm of this Pent house at the 7th floor Matrah heights being surrounded by castle mountains bays and forts. The view itself would take you on a relaxing scenery,quiet and well ventilated. Our pleasure to assist you with any queries at any time of the day be it by phone email or text or in person Be ready to stay in a serene place where u get to relax and enjoy at the same time the place is great for tourist as it is a center of attraction in Muscat. Places of interest nearby *Matrah souq (5mins away by foot) *Matrah fort and ports (all in the same area) *Matrah corniche (same area) *National Museum and Al Alam Palace (same area) *Al Riyam park and Geotrek (same area) * Qantab heights and beaches (10 mins away drive) * Al Bustan Palace Hotel and Barr Al Jissa shangrila Hotel (10 mins away drive) *Al Qurum Shatti beach (lovers baywalk) watersports activities are in the same area and Rose Garden (10 mins away drive) *Royal Opera House (10 mins away drive) *Grand Mosque (15 mins away drive) *Al Amerat Heights (20 mins drive) Omans Most visited Places distance from the Apartment *Wadi Shab and Tiwi Beach (167km around 1hr and 45 mins away by car) *Sinkhole Bimmah (125km 1 hr and 15 mins away by car) place is next to wadi shab *Bandar Khayran u can do kayaking in reasonable price (33km around 25mins drive) *Wahiba Sands (220km about 2 and half drive) *Wadi Bani Khalid is before wahiba sands u can drop by before going for a camp *Jabal Akdhar ( 192km roughly 2hrs drive) *Jabal shams (180km roughly 2 hrs drive) *Dimanyat Island watersports activities (30 mins drive to al mouj then rent a boat to the island) *Salalah 1200km 8 to hrs drive"}]

column95: [{"date":"2020-02-09T10:03:51.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-05-16T08:27:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"Ali and Tina were amazing hosts and we really enjoyed staying in their lovely home. They went out of their way to make sure we had the best time in Muscat, with lots of great tips. I would definitely recommend their place to stay.","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/40602283"],"username":"Ian"},{"date":"2020-02-05T12:30:11.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-05-16T08:27:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"Non potevo fare scelta migliore per questo breve ma intenso soggiorno a Muscat. Fin dai primi messaggi scambiati per prenotare, Tina è stata veloce e molto disponibile ad accogliere le mie richieste. Ha organizzato per me un passaggio dall’aeroporto di prima mattina, fuori dall’orario previsto per il check in e poi mi ha accolta con the, frutta e dolci prendendosi il tempo di darmi informazioni per muovermi in zona. Grazie al contatto che mi ha creato con Khalid, suo amico altrettanto generoso e gentile, che gestisce un ostello per donne, ho potuto fare un trekking in zona e vivere due giornate fuori dalle rotte turistiche in posti bellissimi. Tina è sempre stata generosa e disponibile in ogni momento e mi ha offerto ottime colazioni. La camera è come nelle foto, il letto molto comodo ed il terrazzino ha una bella e ampia vista. Wifi perfetto. La posizione dell’alloggio è strategica, secondo me la migliore per visitare Muscat, ho potuto girare un intero giorno comodamente a piedi, visitando il forte, il mercato e il souk e camminando sulla Corniche fino alla città vecchia. Per me una esperienza estremamente positiva! Spero di poter tornare..","sourceURLs":["https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/40602283"],"username":"Anna"},{"date":"2019-12-26T11:49:35.000Z","dateSeen":"2021-05-16T08:27:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"text":"Apartment looks just like the photos. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2023-03-25T07:04:00.000Z","value":"You'll love our 15-acre, organic date and fruit farm in interior Oman. A unique destination, our 4 air-conditioned, self-catering 1-bedroom cabins with outdoor BBQ/kitchen, games room, and pool access, are a perfect ‘back to nature’ retreat for couples or singles. Explore the ancient forts, market-towns and villages of the historic Ash Sharqiyyah region, or simply sit back and enjoy the scenery, sunsets and star-lit skies from the privacy of your small terrace.We have 1 king and 3 twin air-conditioned cabins to choose from. Neem Eco-cabin is one of our three twin cabins and has a field view. See our other listings for Sidr and Luban twins and Bedam, our King-size special.All our cabins are designed to resemble traditional date palm shelters of the neighbouring Bedouin but with maximum comfort in mind. The three twin cabins, including Neem, are furnished with sprung mattress European-size luxury twin beds and the fourth with a King-size bed and padded headboards. Hotel-quality cotton sheets and towels are provided.] Hotel-grade cotton bedding and towels are provided. The modern bathroom suite with rainshower is stocked with eco-friendly products. Your private kitchenette is equipped with a Whirlpool fridge/freezer, granite counter-top, kettle, coffee plunger, supplies and all utensils and crockery. A wardrobe provides hanging and shelf storage for longer stays. The four cabins are offset from each other for maximum privacy, a short distance from a central area landscaped with shade and fruits trees, aloe and lemon grass for sitting and cooking in a purpose-built BBQ kitchen shaded by a date palm roof. All utensils and crockery are provided. Outdoor space for guests comprises:-•A small private terrace with table and chairs;•a central purpose-built, roofed, BBQ kitchen and landscaped dining area;•Barasti-enclosed game room with table tennis table;•Large air-conditioned traditional ‘majlis’ reception for reading, relaxation and board games •Walking perimeter track.We cannot promise you silence; you will awaken to birdsong and bees humming in the trees, and sleep to the sound of a rustling breeze and background chatter of crickets. We can promise however a beautiful natural setting, fresh air and wide-open spaces in which to relax, wind-down and switch off (literally and metaphorically). While the Oasis is in a secluded location, it is only a 5 minute drive to the nearest village, 15 minutes from 2 large supermarkets in Samad Al Shan, 20 minutes from the new Muscat-Sur six-lane highway and less than 90 minutes from Muscat International Airport. The market towns of Sinaw (30 minutes), Ibra (45 minutes) and Nizwa/Izki/Manah/Adam (60 minutes) are an easy day trip away.The Oasis has phone reception and 4G signal. We are happy to provide a local sim card for the duration of your visit.Regrettably, we cannot accommodate extra guests. Depending on our schedule, we may be able to cater for a later check-in time than the one listed. Let us know when booking if you think you might need this. Contact us if you wish to book more than six months ahead.Guests are free to explore the Oasis keeping to the main paths and pick fruit, herbs and vegetables when in season. Play table tennis in our outdoor games room or sit and read a book or play a board game in the comfort of our large reception majlis/common room. Please note that the outdoor BBQ kitchen, pool, games room and reception majlis are open to all guests. Depending on whether other cabins are booked you may be sharing these spaces with us and upto 6 other travellers.After a day exploring the nearby towns and villages of the historic Ash Sharqiyyah region, the camel enclosures outside the gate, or nearby Wadi Daqeeq, cool off with a relaxing swim in our infinity swimming pool of fresh water drawn from an artesian well (set timings). Please note as this is a desert farm you may encounter all manner of small creatures and bugs. We cannot rule out the occasional scorpion or grass snake. For this reason we advise keeping to paths and cleared ground and consider it unsuitable for children.We will usually be on hand at the farm and contactable by phone. If for any reason, we are not immediately available, there will always be someone on hand at the property to assist you. We are happy to give you recommendations during your stay should you so wish but otherwise will leave you to enjoy the peace and tranquillity.House rulesBoth men and women are required to dress modestly in and around the OasisNo shoes in the cabinQuiet time after 10.00pmNo additional guests in the cabinCheck in 1-6pmCheck out 11.00amAdvance booking 6 monthsMinimum stay – 2 nightsContact me for further information or queries."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2022-08-02T15:34:00.000Z","value":"SAMT GUEST HOUSE is a three bedroomed home on the magical island of Masirah. The spacious home can accommodate 10 persons comfortably with indoor and outdoor living areas, private swimming pool with shower room, outdoor barbeque area dn bar, and children's playground. A large living room with wall mounted flat screen TV leads to a well equipped spacious dining area and kitchen. Each bedroom has its own en suite shower room and wall mounted TV. Masirah Island is the largest island 19 km off Oman's beautiful coast. The island offers the following activities for guests:* Hiking* Fishing* Diving* Snorkelling* Kite Surfing* Surf boardingFrom the mainland of Oman the journey to the island is by way of the ferry from Barr Al Hikman. This paradise can appeal to the keen watersports enthusiast, the young family with children, or those who just want to get away from it all and chill. The pool and playground at Samt Guest House are enclosed within the walled property where children and adults can enjoy ample activities in the safety of an enclosed property while having the superb position of being located directly on the beach. Guests at Samt Guest House will no doubt experience first hand the wonderful hospitality that Omanis are so renowned for. Fishing charters can be arranged as can a tour guide for those guests who want to explore this unique and magical part of the world. Turtle and dolphin watching, kite surfing, deep sea fishing, and beach combing, are just a few of the exciting experiences offered by Masirah Island."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2021-11-23T17:44:00.000Z","value":"Enjoy the best of lifestyle resort and leisure by crystal-blue waters at Millennium Resort Mussanah. Experience perfect relaxation, with panoramic views over the Hajar Mountains and the Gulf of Oman. The world-class outdoor sporting facilities in our resort include an 18-hole mini-golf course, tennis courts, and 4 Swimming Pools and 1 Children’s Pool, of which one is exclusive to families, Zipline, floating water park “Aqua Fun”, PADI dive center. Our resort’s private 54-berth marina allows for water sport, sailing, snorkeling and yacht charter options, as well as customized holiday packages and excursions.Our exceptional beach resort in Musssanah has been the recipient of multiple awards from 2015 MENA Travel, 2017 & 2018 World Luxury Hotels, 2017 Luxury Travel Guide, 2018 Hotel Middle East Award, 2018 Arabian Travel Awards, 2018 Haute Grandeur Awards and TripAdvisor. With 308 spacious accommodations a state-of-the-art Health & Fitness Club and Zayna Spa offering relaxation treatments from around the world, couples, families and business guests will be sure of a restful stay at our luxury resort in Oman. Kids and adults will love the on-site diving and sailing school, zip-line and aqua fun. Come stay, live and play in the lap of luxury. For those who wish to explore the local area, Rustaq & Nakhal Fort, the Harjar Mountains, Mussanah Fort and Damaniyat Island are all nearby, as well as a local fish market. Twice a week, the resort provides the shuttle service for a round-trip to the Muscat Mall for those guests who love shopping."}]
